# Phase 1a — homepage redesign foundations (visibility + defaultLeagueId)

## M1 — Schema audit + visibility mapping decided

### Field name finding

The recruiting flag is `League.recruiting Boolean @default(false)` in
`prisma/schema.prisma:182` — NOT `recruitingMode` as the briefing
hypothesised. Same column drives the banner today.

### Per-league migration mapping (one-shot backfill)

```
recruiting = true   → visibility = 'PUBLIC_OPEN'    (banner visible, apply-flow OPEN)
recruiting = false  → visibility = 'PUBLIC_CLOSED'  (banner hidden, apply-flow OPEN by direct link)
                    →                               (PRIVATE is opt-in via admin toggle post-deploy;
                                                     no league becomes PRIVATE on backfill)
```

Default for new leagues: `PUBLIC_CLOSED` (admins explicitly opt in to
PUBLIC_OPEN — same conservative default that `recruiting` had).

### `League.recruiting` call sites (6)

1. `src/lib/leagueFlags.ts:39` — canonical banner gate (fed into Dashboard's `recruiting` prop).
2. `src/components/Dashboard.tsx:329` — banner conditional render (consumes the prop).
3. `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts:125` — `applyToLeague` rejects when false.
4. `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts:428` — `registerToLeague` rejects when false.
5. `src/app/recruit/[slug]/page.tsx:65` — `/recruit/<slug>` form-page gate.
6. `src/components/admin/SettingsTab.tsx:82` — admin toggle UI state.

### Behaviour mapping by visibility (post-PR)

| Site                              | PUBLIC_OPEN | PUBLIC_CLOSED | PRIVATE |
|-----------------------------------|-------------|---------------|---------|
| RecruitingBanner (via leagueFlags)| visible     | hidden        | hidden  |
| `applyToLeague` action            | accept      | accept        | reject  |
| `registerToLeague` action         | accept      | accept        | reject  |
| `/recruit/<slug>` page            | render form | render form   | reject  |
| Admin toggle                      | radio: open | radio: closed | radio: private |

PRIVATE is the strict gate — applications go through the invite path
(`/join/<code>`) instead. CLOSED is "open to direct link, just not
advertised" per the user's spec.

### `User.defaultLeagueId` plan

Nullable FK to `League.id` (`onDelete: SetNull` so league delete doesn't
cascade-delete the user). No index per briefing. Updates land in
Phase 1c (multi-league switcher); this PR ships the column only.

### `League.isDefault` per Q3

Keep the column. Add a TODO comment noting it's a candidate for removal
once the dashboard work fully replaces its current consumers
(`leagueSlugServer.getDefaultLeagueId`, `matchday/[id]/page.tsx` route
disambiguation, `account/player/page.tsx` per-membership sort, etc.).
Behavior unchanged in this PR.

### Tests touching `league.recruiting`

- `tests/unit/preseasonRecruitingToggles.test.ts` — exercises `getLeagueFlags`
  return shape; will need updating to also reflect visibility-derived flags.
- `tests/unit/v182_multi_position_validation.test.ts` — sets
  `recruiting: true` in mock data; safe to leave (`recruiting` column
  still present, dual-write).

## M2 — Migration drafted + admin toggle wired

### Migration `20260517000000_league_visibility_and_user_default_league`

- Creates `LeagueVisibility` enum (`PRIVATE` / `PUBLIC_CLOSED` / `PUBLIC_OPEN`).
- Adds `League.visibility` NOT NULL DEFAULT `'PUBLIC_CLOSED'`.
- One-shot backfill: `recruiting=true → PUBLIC_OPEN`, `recruiting=false → PUBLIC_CLOSED`.
- Adds `User.defaultLeagueId TEXT NULL` with `ON DELETE SET NULL` FK to `League`.

### Per-league migration result (mapping for review)

```
SELECT id, name, recruiting, 'PUBLIC_OPEN' OR 'PUBLIC_CLOSED' as visibility
FROM "League"
ORDER BY "createdAt"
```

Every league with `recruiting=true` becomes PUBLIC_OPEN; every other
league becomes PUBLIC_CLOSED. PRIVATE is opt-in via the new admin
toggle post-deploy. Operator should sanity-check the `League` row count
matches expected after deploy via `SELECT visibility, COUNT(*) FROM "League" GROUP BY 1`.

### Admin UI placement

- New server action: `setLeagueVisibility` in
  `src/app/admin/leagues/actions.ts` (next to the legacy
  `setLeagueRecruiting`, which now dual-writes).
- `SettingsTab.tsx` swaps the binary "Recruiting On/Off" buttons for a
  three-radio "Visibility" section (Private / Public — closed /
  Public — open). Sits in the same slot, between Pre-season mode and
  League details.
- `League` interface gains `visibility: 'PRIVATE' | 'PUBLIC_CLOSED' | 'PUBLIC_OPEN'`.
- All admin tokens (`bg-admin-surface`, `text-admin-text*`, `border-admin-*`)
  per the admin-orthogonal-UX rule. Test-IDs:
  - `settings-tab-visibility-section`
  - `settings-tab-visibility-private`
  - `settings-tab-visibility-public-closed`
  - `settings-tab-visibility-public-open`

## M3 — RecruitingBanner re-gated + apply path updated

### Sites updated

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `src/lib/leagueFlags.ts` | Reads `visibility`; returns `recruiting = visibility === 'PUBLIC_OPEN'` plus a new raw `visibility` field on `LeagueFlags`. |
| `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts` (`applyToLeague`) | Gate flips from `if (!league.recruiting)` to `if (visibility === 'PRIVATE')`. PUBLIC_OPEN + PUBLIC_CLOSED both accept submissions. |
| `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts` (`registerToLeague`) | Same gate flip. |
| `src/app/recruit/[slug]/page.tsx` | Page-level gate flips: PRIVATE → "Not currently recruiting" surface; PUBLIC_OPEN + PUBLIC_CLOSED → render form. |

### Sites unchanged on purpose

- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx:329` — still consumes `recruiting` prop
  from `LeagueFlags`. Prop semantics unchanged ("show banner"); only
  the upstream source of truth moved.
- `setLeagueRecruiting` server action still exists and now dual-writes
  visibility (`true → PUBLIC_OPEN`, `false → PUBLIC_CLOSED`). Kept for
  one cycle in case any external/test caller still uses it.

